      • prepareAttribute

        protected void prepareAttribute​(StringBuilder handlers,
                                String name,
                                Object value)
        If this label is describes a required field, then the CSS style class attribute gets appended with the "required" style, if not null, which takes effect for both the normal and error style.

        Parameters:

      • prepareValue

        protected void prepareValue​(StringBuilder handlers)
        Performs any pre-processing on the value property before printing it. The default behavior is to append an asterik inside a span tag with a CSS class attribute of getRequiredStyleClass(), if the required property is set.
        Parameters:
        handlers - The StringBuilder that output will be appended to.
        See Also:
        getRequiredStyleClass()
